From: Claude AI Assistant
Date: Thu, 6 Feb 2025 05:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Alt+character combinations for BlackBerry physical keyboard

The BlackBerry keyboard's alt+character mappings (e.g., Alt+W='1') were
producing invisible characters instead of the expected symbols.

Root cause: The keyboard_layout_english_us overlay was being applied via
KeyCharacterMap::combine(), which overwrites keys using insert_or_assign().
This replaced stmpe.kcm's 5-behavior keys (including alt) with the overlay's
4-behavior keys (no alt), causing alt behaviors to be lost at runtime.

Solution: Skip overlay application for stmpe_keypad device in EventHub,
allowing stmpe.kcm to have full priority without being overwritten.

Changes:
- EventHub.cpp: Skip overlay for stmpe_keypad built-in keyboard
- stmpe.kcm: Use explicit capslock definitions and alt mappings

Tested-by: BlackBerry KEY2 (athena)
---
 frameworks/native/services/inputflinger/reader/EventHub.cpp | 6 ++++++
 device/blackberry/sdm660-common/configs/keylayout/keychars/stmpe.kcm | 3 ++-
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/frameworks/native/services/inputflinger/reader/EventHub.cpp b/frameworks/native/services/inputflinger/reader/EventHub.cpp
index 1234567..abcdef9 100644
--- a/frameworks/native/services/inputflinger/reader/EventHub.cpp
+++ b/frameworks/native/services/inputflinger/reader/EventHub.cpp
@@ -1547,6 +1547,12 @@ bool EventHub::setKeyboardLayoutOverlay(int32_t deviceId, std::shared_ptr<KeyCh
     if (device == nullptr || device->keyMap.keyCharacterMap == nullptr) {
         return false;
     }
+
+    // Skip overlay for stmpe keyboard - it has complete custom mappings
+    if (device->identifier.name == "stmpe_keypad") {
+        ALOGW("EventHub: Skipping overlay for stmpe_keypad - using native kcm layout");
+        return false;
+    }
 
     if (map == nullptr) {
         device->keyMap.keyCharacterMap->clearLayoutOverlay();
